	   <tr><td colspan=2>Allright I think I might have screwed up Royaly, but maybe you guys can prove that I didnt.<br>I had a lv 14 Cleric transfered all my stuff to a new Paladin. I didnt like the cleric because It was giving me a headache just trying to level because there are very few places they can fight, and I did not have a high lv druid friend that was willing to port me all around :(<br>As a Paladin what skills should I be working up other than my primary weapon skills and such..<br>Should I bother spending Practice points on Taunt? I heard that having a high Taunt skill is great when trying to protect casters. <br>I need all the Info you can give me on the subject matter of playing a Paladin because I dont want my deletion of my cleric to be in vain. Also if any of you are high lv Paladins out there on the E'ci server look me up if you have your own guild or something(maybe I can join)<br><br>Shanra<br>~former Cleric gone Paladin~<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
